ZH: 我正在学习如何驾驶汽车并掌握方向盘的技巧。
EN: I am learning how to drive a car and master the skills of steering the steering wheel.

ZH: 她紧握方向盘，专注地驾驶着。
EN: She tightly grips the steering wheel and drives attentively.

ZH: 这辆车的方向盘很容易操作。
EN: The steering wheel of this car is easy to operate.

ZH: 他扭动方向盘以改变车子的行驶方向。
EN: He turns the steering wheel to change the direction of the car.

ZH: 它的方向盘非常灵敏，反应迅速。
EN: Its steering wheel is very sensitive and reacts quickly.

ZH: 当你转弯时，要轻轻转动方向盘。
EN: When you make a turn, gently turn the steering wheel.

ZH: 你需要时刻把握方向盘以保持车辆的稳定。
EN: You need to always hold the steering wheel to keep the vehicle stable.

ZH: 他的手指紧紧握住方向盘。
EN: His fingers grip the steering wheel tightly.

ZH: 这个方向盘设计得非常舒适，手感好。
EN: This steering wheel is designed to be very comfortable with a good touch.

ZH: 他在方向盘上加装了一个方向盘套来增加摩擦力。
EN: He added a steering wheel cover on the steering wheel to increase friction.

ZH: 方向盘的颜色与车内的内饰相协调。
EN: The color of the steering wheel matches the interior of the car.

ZH: 她把方向盘调整到最合适的位置以便驾驶。
EN: She adjusts the steering wheel to the most suitable position for driving.

ZH: 新车的方向盘很有质感，手感细腻。
EN: The steering wheel of the new car has a high-quality texture and a delicate touch.

ZH: 我们需要保持双手握住方向盘，这样更安全。
EN: We need to keep both hands on the steering wheel for safety.

ZH: 这个方向盘有一个漂亮的标志在中间。
EN: This steering wheel has a beautiful logo in the middle.

ZH: 当你打方向盘时，请确认周围没有障碍物。
EN: When you turn the steering wheel, please make sure there are no obstacles around.

ZH: 我的方向盘需要进行调整，感觉不够直。
EN: My steering wheel needs adjustment, it doesn't feel straight enough.

ZH: 不要随意拧动方向盘，这会导致车辆失控。
EN: Don't twist the steering wheel randomly, it will cause the vehicle to lose control.

ZH: 她的手指在方向盘上轻轻滑过，表现得非常熟练。
EN: Her fingers gently glide over the steering wheel, showing great proficiency.

ZH: 这辆车的方向盘可以进行上下、前后调节。
EN: The steering wheel of this car can be adjusted up and down, and forward and backward.
